valued at $1 billion or more were announced. By Laura M. Holson.
</P>
<P>
   FEDEX-PILOTS (Undated) _ Last week's decision by Federal Express
pilots to suspend their strike threat and accept whatever they
could negotiate with their employer was a stunning victory for the
company. It was the result of a unique corporate culture, a weak
and inexperienced union, and the skillful use of a classic
union-busting strategy. By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
