television and online company formed by Geraldine Laybourne, the
former president of Nickelodeon, has entered into a partnership
with Oprah Winfrey and Carsey-Werner-Mandabach Co. to create a
cable television network aimed at women viewers. By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-CARS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ In another demonstration of
the blurring of the lines between the online and off-line
advertising and media realms, a leading Internet marketer is naming
one of the world's biggest agencies to handle duties ranging from
global brand-building to creating campaigns for television,
magazines and newspapers. By Stuart Elliott.
