<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Advantage goes to early-bird shoppers who get cream of the crop
 &HT;    By Sheila M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Got your eyes set on a special toy for the little
ones?
</P>
<P>
   If so, it pays to shop early.
</P>
<P>
   Several makers of high-tech toys said there are limited supplies
(did you really expect them to say otherwise?) but the early birds
should not have much of a problem.
</P>
<P>
   For example, Lego's Mindstorms robotics building system can be
found in Toys ``R'' Us, Target, Media Play and Zany Brainy. Buyers
can order the set directly by calling 1-800-453-4652.
</P>
<P>
   There's already a run on Furby, the $29.99 furry interactive
creature that is causing quite a stir in toy stores.
</P>
<P>
   If you know the toy you want, it also pays to visit the toy
manufacturer's Web site for more information. Some sites even let
you play games online.
</P>
<P>
   A few sites:
</P>
<P>
   _ Mattel products: http://www.mattelmedia.com
</P>
<P>
   _ Tiger Electronics: http://www.game.com/tigertoys/ntoys.htm
</P>
<P>
   _ Hasbro: http://www.hasbro-interactive.com
</P>
<P>
   Sheila M. Poole writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
