   DIABETES-SCREENINGS _ Instead of screening people for Type II
diabetes at age 45, health workers should get to them at age 25,
when much of the damage from the illness could be prevented. CDC
researchers found there would be a huge cost savings. (Guthrie,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
