<P>
   SIBLEY-COLUMN _ It can't happen to many people since so many
live in new houses nowadays, but a perfectly wonderful occasion for
me was having the descendants of the builders of my cabin drop by
and talk about their ancestors who cut and raised the very logs
that surrounded us. (Sibley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOG-SHELTER _ A sometimes happy/mostly sad story about what goes
on behind the scenes when dogs are brought into a typical animal
shelter. Our story begins in Dayton, Ohio, and tells tails (sorry)
of scared animals, frustrated shelter workers and frantic owners
looking for lost pets. (Dempsey, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BOY-DONATION _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Chris Anderson, 11, decided what
to do with that birthday money he'd been saving: donate it to needy
persons in Honduras whose lives were wrecked from Hurricane Mitch.
Then he challenged his parents to match his donation. Soon, the
local Red Cross received $500 because of this youngster's
determination. (Huffman, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
