<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Now that it looks as though they'll be able to
save their president from impeachment, and with the general
concurrence of the public, the next task for congressional
Democrats is to figure out how to distance themselves from him in
ways that same public notices and credits. For while most Americans
do not want President Clinton impeached, neither do they want him
absolved. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for Cox
Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ It was with wry curiosity that I read, last
weekend, of yet another cult that believes the days of our
existence are fatally linked to the end of the millennium. What so
many have forgotten to take into consideration are all the
calendars of all the religions. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist
for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Don't we all long for a world where
two plus two always adds up to four? It doesn't. Not when one day
you're healthy as a horse and the next you're lying on an examining
table wearing a hankie-sized piece of cotton wondering if you'll
survive the chemotherapy. That doesn't add up. (Kabat, Waco
Herald-Tribune) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SKUBE-COLUMN _ The two Tom Wolfes. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ The December Texas Highways
magazine is out containing a readers' poll about the best places in
Texas. Waco is not one of them according to this list. That may
offend some, but is somewhat understandable. (Young, Waco Tribune
Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Remind me never to go
shopping with my son again. Each time I do, it's just like the time
before. Only worse. The size of the purchase makes no difference.
Our exchanges heat up just the same whether it's computers or
sneakers. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
