<HEADLINE>
ENCHANTED ROCK: IF YOU GO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1998 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Getting there: Enchanted Rock State Natural Area is 88 miles
from San Antonio, taking Interstate 10 northwest and exiting on
U.S. Highway 87 toward Fredericksburg. At Fredericksburg, turn
right on Ranch Road 965. The park is 17 miles north.
</P>
<P>
   Admission: $5 per person. Children 12 and younger are admitted
free.
</P>
<P>
   Hours: The park is open seven days a week year-round. Day use
hours are 8 a.m. to 10 p.m. On peak days, such as weekends and
holidays, the park is closed after reaching an admission limit,
reopening at 7 p.m. to additional visitors.
</P>
<P>
   For more information: Enchanted Rock State Natural Area, Route
4, Box 170, Fredericksburg, Texas 78624. Ranger station,
915-247-3903; state park reservations, 512-389-8900. For the latest
information on park conditions, call 800-792-1112.
</P>
