<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Cox News Service spot news budget for WEDNESDAY, NOV. 25,
1998.
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   RENO-GORE _ WASHINGTON _ Tuesday is the deadline for Attorney
General Janet Reno to decide whether to seek an independent counsel
in the Justice Department's investigation of Vice President Al
Gore's alleged fund-raising activities from his White House office.
The decision and what it may mean. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Continuing spot coverage of the
Microsoft antitrust trial. (Regan, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   LENDERS _ WASHINGTON _ The National Community Reinvestment
Coalition holds a news conference to release ``America's Best and
Worst Lenders,'' a report that uses the Home Mortgage Disclosure
Act to rank and analyze the top 50 lenders in the 20 largest
metropolitan areas from 1994 through 1997. (Monroe, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   POLICE-NOTICKETS _ ATLANTA _ Fed up with the prospect of yet
another year with no pay raises and possibly no uniform allowances,
as well as loss of other benefits, Atlanta officers are threatening
a one-day work action that could leave the city $100,000 short.
They call it ``no ticket Friday'' and it's planned for Dec. 4, a
day when no tickets will be written by any Atlanta police officer.
(Longa, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PBP-PILOT-VIAGRA (DEVELOPING) _ Investigators are trying to
determine whether the medication Viagra played a role in the death
of William Knight, who died in a plane crash over the weekend. The
drug can affect perception of colors. (Pickel, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   PBP-OFFICER-ARRESTED (20 inches) _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _
Veteran West Palm Beach Police Officer Louis Berry was arrested by
his own department Tuesday on charges he systematically abused a
court program that pays witnesses for testifying.
</P>
<P>
   The arrest, which came after a `Palm Beach Post' investigation
revealed irregularities in payments made to Berry, highlights the
lack of a dependable system of checks and balances in how the
payments are made to certain types of witnesses and inefficiencies
in other areas of witness payment. Berry, 41, was charged with
official misconduct and grand theft Tuesday after a meeting with
criminal and internal investigators. (Gonzalez, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   TRIPLE-MURDER _ ATLANTA _ Murder indictment expected of Timothy
Carl Dawson in the Hilton Hotel killings. (Croft, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   JOURNAL-BRITAIN _ LONDON _ A letter home about driving in
London. It's hilarious. Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in both (i) International and (k) Commentary
categories.
</P>
<P>
   This is the Cox News Service spot news budget for Friday, April
3, 1998. We will update this budget at 6 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   Separate feature and commentary budgets move at 10 a.m. ET
Monday-Friday. Separate sports and business budgets move at 5 p.m.
Monday-Friday.
</P>
