<P>
   For close to two decades, mathematicians and physicists have
been flocking to the stock market. Is their success a triumph of
science _ or just dumb luck? Gary Taubes, a contributing editor at
Discover magazine, reports. Taubes won the 1997 Pan American Health
Organization award for excellence in international health
reporting.
</P>
