   &UR; LIFE ON ICE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ONE COLOR SLIDE &QL; 
 &UR; (700 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KATHY A SVITIL &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   What might life be like on Mars or on Jupiter's moon Europa? It
may very well resemble some remarkable microbes recently discovered
in Antarctica's frigid deserts. Kathy A. Svitil, an associate
editor at Discover magazine, reports.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-LIFE-ON-ICE-NYTSF. Sent to category codes ``l''
lifestyle and ``a'' general news.
