<P>
   SIXLEGGED-TURKEYS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Come Thanksgiving, Fox Sports knows it's going to be
hearing from animal rights activists. Seems they have a problem
with the six-legged turkey that John Maddden, NFL color analyst for
Fox, uses as a prop for Thanksgiving Day football games. Joe Pat
Fieseler, who owns a hideaway barbeque place in south Irving, is
the man behind the creation and he'll be cooking up another
multi-legged bird this week for Madden, who in turn will carve it
up and hand out ``turkey leg awards'' to the most valuable players
of the game between Dallas and Minnesota. By GORDON DICKSON. Story
will move, POSSIBLY LATE, in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I found a bag of cookies in my kitchen today. Old,
stale cookies. They were in a lower cabinet, behind the crockpot I
never use. How did a bag of cookies live and die in a household
with two rapidly growing males and one snack-happy dad? Well, I ate
three cookies and hid the bag from them, that's how. I just forgot
where I hid them until now. Wait, let me explain. I am not crazy.
By MONICA ANDERSON. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The truth about Daryl Hannah's hand, the origin of the
term ``hard-wired,'' other trivia. By ROGERS CADENHEAD. Story will
move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SWINDELL-BOOKSHELF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Upon learning that the ``upset'' winner of the
National Book Award for fiction is Alice McDermott for ``Charming
Billy,'' I was somewhat surprised but more elated. I really wanted
McDermott to win, for the needed recognition it can bring her, and
because ``Charming Billy'' is a strong work. By LARRY SWINDELL.
Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F O O D &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
