   NYTBOOK-QUARTET-NYTSF, INDIVISIBLE BY FOUR, A String Quartet in
Pursuit of Harmony. By Arnold Steinhardt.
</P>
<P>
   308 pp. New York: Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux. $25. The first
violinist of the Guarneri Quartet recounts a harmonious 35-year
career.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-MOVIES-NYTSF, TOTALLY, TENDERLY, TRAGICALLY, Essays and
Criticism From a Lifelong Love Affair With the Movies. By Phillip
Lopate. 384 pp. New York: Anchor Books/Doubleday. Paper, $12.95.
Phillip Lopate has been mad about movies his entire life.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-BERLIN-1000&AMP;ADD-NYTSF, ISAIAH BERLIN, By Michael
Ignatieff. Illustrated. 356 pp. New York: Metropolitan Books/
</P>
<P>
   Henry Holt &AMP; Company. $30. Isaiah Berlin's big idea was that
there isn't any big idea.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-CAPITALISM-NYTSF, THE CRISIS OF GLOBAL CAPITALISM Open
Society Endangered. By George Soros. 245 pp. New York: Public
Affairs. $26. If the world's most famous money manager is alarmed,
let's all get hysterical at once.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-MARSHALL-NYTSF, THURGOOD MARSHALL: AMERICAN
REVOLUTIONARY. By Juan Williams. Illustrated. 459 pp. New York:
Times Books/Random House. $27.50 For 'one of America's leading
radicals,' the weapon of choice was the United States Constitution.
