 This ``separate buy'' article is from Latin Trade magazine,
America's leading journal of Latin American business, finance and
trade: &HT;    BIG BLACK AND BLUE. IBM has taken a publicity beating as
corruption charges taint subsidiaries in Argentina and elsewhere.
Big Blue's experience reveals a challenge faced by all
multinationals: How to ensure that corporate ethics practiced at
home are followed overseas.
 &HT;    Filed as BC-IBM-CORRUPTION-LATINTRADE-NYTSF.
