<P>
   FBC-GATORS-JOHNSON _ A tape of the pregame scuffle before the
FSU-Florida game shows Gator quarterback Doug Johnson throwing a
football in the direction of FSU head coach Bobby Bowden. Johnson,
standing on the edge of the large swarm of players mixing it up at
midfield, can clearly be seen getting a football from a Florida
manager and throwing a line-drive that strikes F6SU student
assistant strength coach Eric Johnson in the back of the head. Eric
Johnson is shown standing about 5 feet from Bowden as the ball
ricochets high off the student-assistant's head. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA-GATECH _ Matchup story on Georgia's passing game vs.
Tech's passing defense. One of the keys in Saturday's
Georgia-Georgia Tech game will be the UGA passing game, led by
Quincy Carter and Champ Bailey, against the Tech passing defense.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH-HAMILTON _ Joe Hamilton has been the player of the
week in the ACC several times during his career, earned MVP honors
at the Carquest Bowl and has led his team to a share of the ACC
title this season. But there's one thing missing from his resume -
a victory over Georgia. If the Jackets hope to end their seven-game
losing streak against their rivals, Hamilton will have to play one
of his better games of the season. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GASOUTHERN _ After a week off, Georgia Southern returns to
action Saturday in its Division I-AA playoff opener against
Colgate. As the top seed in the 16-team field, Georgia Southern
will have home-field advantage as long as it remains alive in the
playoffs. The championship game is scheduled for Dec. 19 at Finley
Stadium in Chattanooga. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUBURN _ ATLANTA _ Interim Auburn coach Bill Oliver has
withdrawn his name from consideration for the Auburn job, leading
the speculation that the school is close to hiring a replacement
for Terry Bowden, who quit Oct. 23. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BB0-BISHER-COLUMN _ Furman Bisher on Ted Williams. (Bisher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS-MARE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The stereotype of a
placekicker is this: He seems to fit into an NFL locker room like
Kate Moss fits in a Weight Watchers meeting. He is small. He can do
little more than kick a ball a long way. He can't tackle. He grew
up thousands of miles away, not knowing the difference between a
touchback and a touchdown. Beano Cook once said, ``The two most
important jobs in America are held by foreigners _ room service and
field-goal kicking.'' Olindo Mare, of course, proves this wrong.
(Woods, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
