   COMPUTER-TEXTBOOKS _ Television did not doom radio, video did
not kill film and electronic publishing will not likely end print.
But, suddenly, many discern the start of a critical mass shifting
publishing for reference works, handbooks and textbooks to the
digital realm. And there are those who say they can see the day
when books will be viewed ``more as objets d'art than things we use
all the time.'' By Ethan Bronner.
