   CLASS _ GREENSBORO, N.C._The U.S. Civil Rights Commission has
agreed to look into a college course that critics have condemned as
racist because it depicted slaves as happy defenders of the South.
However, commissioners concede that the course probably does not
constitute a civil rights violation and plan to expand their probe
to look at other aspects of race relations in North Carolina.
(Burritt, Cox News Service)
</P>
