</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Powerchicks and other birds
 &HT;    By Richard L. Eldredge
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   What happens when Powerchicks meet Dirty Birds?
</P>
<P>
   We're not sure it'll be pretty, but at least it'll be on
national TV. So says Matt Towery, who on Tuesday, promised Buzz
that his Dec. 8 appearance on ABC's ``Politically Incorrect With
Bill Maher'' will promote more than his new book, ``Powerchicks:
How Women Will Dominate America.''
</P>
<P>
   He'll also be braggin' on an old love, the red-hot Atlanta
Falcons.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm gonna wear some sort of Falcons jersey on the air,'' said
Towery, 39, an Atlanta native who started going to games in 1966.
``They've been losing for so many years, and now that they're
finally winning, I want the rest of America to know that we've got
the best football team.''
</P>
<P>
   Already in its second printing, ``Powerchicks'' could make
Towery one of Atlanta's better-known authors _ and not just because
Tom Wolfe has finally left town. The former state legislator and
occasional Las Vegas stand-up comedian swears he won't forget the
Falcons on ``Correct,'' a late-night current events talk show with
a comical bent. He may even dance for them.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can do the `Dirty Bird' and if Bill Maher asks me to do it
on the air,'' Towery pledged, ``I will.''
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: buzz(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   For more juicy gossip and keen commentary, see what Vixana has
to say on http://www.ajc.com.
</P>
