   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, Nov. 25 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY-HELP-HASSLE (Los Angeles) _ With the economy in high
gear and unemployment at generational lows, there is a glut of
unfilled holiday positions. ``It even gets down to people being
afraid there will be a shortage of people to play Santa in the
malls,'' said one local economist. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
