<SLUG> BC-FBC-TEXAS-A&AMP;M-HOLDMAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEXAS A&AMP;M'S WARRICK HOLDMAN THRIVES IN THE SHADOWS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLLEGE STATION, Texas _ The reason Texas A&AMP;M outside linebacker
Warrick Holdman is not recognized as the star player on the team's
``Wrecking Crew'' perhaps can be summarized best one way _ Dat
Nguyen.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dat has done a great job this year,'' said linebacker
Cornelius Anthony, who plays alongside the Butkus Award finalist.
``But if we didn't have a guy like Dat on the team, then Warrick
probably would be the center of attention.''
</P>
<P>
   Living in the shadows as the Aggies head into the regular-season
finale Friday against Texas doesn't bother Holdman, who has twice
as many third-down tackles as his more famous teammate. Holdman
smiles in anticipation of the query.
</P>
<P>
   ``People look at Dat first and then say, `Oh yeah, they've got
some other linebackers,''' Holdman said. ``But Dat and I have been
friends for five years now, and I'm happy for any recognition he
gets. And when Dat makes a big play, I try to get in there, too _
so they'll say Holdman was also in on that play. So I use him some
whenever I can. And I feel like if I just keep playing hard,
someone is going to notice.''
</P>
<P>
   If anyone is disturbed by Holdman's relative lack of
recognition, it's Nguyen.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel terrible about it,'' Nguyen said earlier in the year.
``Every time Warrick does something, they compare him to me.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a huge part of our success. He makes plays left and
right, but people still want to talk to me. I don't know why. Maybe
it's my nationality.''
</P>
<P>
   Doubtful. But a fact.
</P>
<P>
   ``If Dat isn't the name that he is,'' coach R.C. Slocum said,
``then all of a sudden you say this Warrick Holdman is making some
pretty big plays for you.''
</P>
<P>
   Statistics back up Slocum.
</P>
<P>
   Holdman's 22 third-down tackles are two more than Nguyen's 1997
team-leading total. Holdman also leads the team in sacks (7),
passes broken up (8) and pressures (4). His 15 tackles for losses
are only three less than Nguyen's.
</P>
<P>
   Holdman's 79 total tackles trail only those racked up by the two
inside linebackers _ Nguyen (118) and Anthony (87). Considering
that Holdman plays only on one (the left) side of the defense, that
may be the most amazing statistic of them all.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of the plays that go away from him, you still find him
in the tackle somewhere because he's such a good athlete,'' safety
Rich Coady said.
</P>
<P>
   He's also a determined athlete.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted to make a statement this year,'' Holdman said. ``I
came into the year determined to cut loose, have fun and whatever
happens, happens.''
</P>
<P>
   The senior's biggest statements are hard to pick out. He has
three double-digit tackle games. But his play in the victory over
Nebraska is perhaps most memorable. Holdman recovered a fumble in
the end zone, sacked quarterback Bobby Newcombe, made two other
tackles for losses and batted down a pass attempt.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was one of the most exciting games I've played in,''
Holdman said. ``A beautiful day, the crowd was hyped, a big game
with a high-ranked team in our stadium. It was big, but Texas is
bigger than Nebraska. Here, we know we can't lose to Texas.''
</P>
<P>
   That Ricky Williams is only 63 yards away from becoming college
football's all-time leading rusher adds to the game's aura, Holdman
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``It makes our defense stand out even more. Everyone is really
going to be watching the Wrecking Crew to see how we control Ricky,
how we control their offense, really.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going into the game with two things on my mind _ making
sure tackles on Ricky and putting pressure on the quarterback. If
Ricky gets the record, I'll be happy for him. But if we worry too
much about him, they'll beat us with the passing game.''
</P>
<P>
   Expect Holdman to be heavily involved in both areas.
</P>
<P>
   ``Coaches always say that if you have a good year, your seniors
have to play well,'' Coady said. ``And Warrick is a guy who's
playing his best football this year.''
</P>
</TEXT>
