<HEADLINE>
STORR STILL HURTING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Even though he recorded a 21-save shutout in
his return to the lineup Saturday night against the Chicago
Blackhawks, Los Angeles Kings goalie Jamie Storr continues to be
bothered by the groin strain he suffered six weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   Storr was scheduled to play Tuesday night for the Long Beach Ice
Dogs, but he felt a twinge during the morning skate and was held
out of the game for precautionary reasons. Instead, Manny Legace
was assigned to the Ice Dogs and served as their backup. Legace is
expected to be recalled by the Kings today on an emergency basis.
</P>
<P>
   Center Jozef Stumpel (sprained ankle) and defenseman Doug Bodger
(broken hand) skated Tuesday, and it appears Bodger is the more
likely of the two to play when the Kings' season resumes against
Phoenix on Saturday night at the Forum. The status of goalie
Stephane Fiset (groin strain) for Saturday's game remains
uncertain.
</P>
</TEXT>
