<SLUG> BC-HKN-DUCKNOT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MIGHTY DUCKS NOTEBOOK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 c.1998 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Teemu Selanne's availability for tonight's
game in Detroit will remain in question up until the pregame skate
at Joe Louis Arena. Selanne, who has missed six games with a thigh
injury, says he hopes to be back. Anaheim Mighty Ducks coach Craig
Hartsburg is also optimistic, but the Ducks and Selanne obviously
don't want to take any chances on the injury becoming a chronic
one.
</P>
<P>
   Selanne had seven goals and 15 points in 13 games before being
injured on Nov. 11 against Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   The Ducks (8-7-4) are 4-2 in Selanne's absence, and Hartsburg
said his star winger may not return to the No. 1 line right away,
especially considering the play of Marty McInnis, who has three
goals and seven points in the six games Selanne has missed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't see much reason to break them up,'' said Hartsburg
after Sunday's win over Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   McInnis has 14 points in 13 games since being acquired by the
Ducks from Chicago, Hartsburg's former team.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't matter where we got him,'' Hartsburg said. ``I'm
just glad we got him. It's been a huge pickup.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a smart player, has good speed, good skill and fits in
well with Paul.''
</P>
<P>
   McInnis' linemates are just as hot as he is. Kariya has a
league-leading nine-game point streak (four goals, 13 points),
while Steve Rucchin has a career-high seven-game streak (four
goals, 11 points).
</P>
<P>
   With the injuries to Selanne, Tomas Sandstrom (broken wrist) and
Travis Green, who strained his knee last Friday against Edmonton,
the Ducks called up forwards Josef Marha and Frank Banham last
weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Green missed the Chicago game and has been ruled out of the
Detroit game, but he is on the trip which continues to Nashville
(Friday), Carolina (Sunday), Pittsburgh (Dec. 1), Chicago (Dec. 3)
and San Jose (Dec. 6).
</P>
<P>
   Marha, a regular who suffered a sprained ankle on opening night,
returned to the lineup for the first time on Friday when he
replaced Green.
</P>
<P>
   Banham, who has spent the season at Cincinnati of the American
Hockey League, will likely be sent back when Green and Selanne are
healthy.
</P>
</TEXT>
